InMobi CFO quits, joins Practo


InMobi Chief Financial Officer (CFO) Manish Dugar has resigned to take up another job, three weeks after 
The Hindu
 reported that the mobile advertising network is laying-off nearly 10 per cent of its staff. “He (Mr. Dugar) left as financial health of the firm (InMobi) is not in a good shape,” said a person with direct knowledge of the development. Mr. Dugar has been appointed as the global CFO of healthcare tech start-up Practo, which provides an app and web service for scheduling appointments with doctors. 
